<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN"
        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<head>
	<title>Moving Divs</title>
	<link type="text/css" href="assets/chap12script08.css" rel="stylesheet" />
	<script type="text/javascript" src="assets/chap12script08.js"></script>

	<style>
		h2 {
    			position: absolute;
    			left: 100px;
    			top: 150px;
			}
	</style>


	<style>
		h3 {
    			position: relative;
    			left: 100px;
    			/***top: 150px;***/
			}
	</style>
</head>
<body>
	<div id="annoyingAdvert">
		This is an incredibly annoying ad of the type you might find on some web sites.
		<div id="closeBox">&otimes;</div>
	</div>
	<p>First section</p>
	
	<p>Second Section</p>
	
	<p>Third Section</p> 
	
	<p>Forth Section</p>

	<h2>This is a heading with an absolute position</h2>

	<p>With absolute positioning, an element can be placed anywhere on a page. The heading below is placed 100px from the left of the page and 150px from the top of the page.</p>

	<h3>This is a heading with an relative position</h3>

	<p>With relative positioning, an element can be placed 100px starting from the above elelement position. So it s offset from paragraph position above.</p>

</body>
</html>